      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "**Key polar features**\n- One **secondary amine (N\u2013H)** in the thiazoline ring (potentially basic, but likely **weakly basic** due to vinylogous/imine-like environment and adjacent heteroatoms).\n- A **tertiary alcohol**: `C(O)(C(F)(F)F)C(F)(F)F` (strong H-bond donor/acceptor; increases polarity).\n- Multiple **fluorinated groups** (two CF3 on the tertiary carbon + OCF2H): increase lipophilicity and size but can also reduce basicity/pKa of nearby amines via inductive effects.",
